# {{PROJECT}} Deployment

Docker Compose + nginx for the three {{PROJECT}} environments (dev, staging, prod).

See [`CLAUDE.md`](./CLAUDE.md) for the full layout, per-env routing details, and operational reference. This README is day-to-day quick-reference only.

## Quick start (dev — local)

```bash
cd dev
cp env.example env/{{PROJECT}}-core.env
cp env.example env/user-service.env
# Fill in third-party keys (Google OAuth, Resend, etc.) if testing those features.
docker compose up
```

Then hit `http://localhost:{{DEV_NGINX_PORT}}/health` to verify and `http://localhost:{{DEV_NGINX_PORT}}{{API_BASE}}/...` for any endpoint.

{{#MONGO}}To also start the Mongo admin UI on `http://localhost:8081` (admin/admin):
```bash
docker compose --profile tools up
```
{{/MONGO}}

## Quick start (staging)

Full from-zero runbook: [`staging/REBUILD.md`](./staging/REBUILD.md). On an existing VM:

```bash
cd /opt/{{PROJECT}}-deployment
sudo docker compose -f staging/docker-compose.yml up -d
```

## Quick start (prod)

**Deferred at bootstrap.** Run `/configure-prod` from the workspace root when ready to publish.

## Environments

| | dev | staging | prod |
|---|---|---|---|
| URL | `http://localhost:{{DEV_NGINX_PORT}}` | `https://{{STAGING_DOMAIN}}` | TODO |
| Compose | `dev/docker-compose.yml` | `staging/docker-compose.yml` | `prod/docker-compose.yml` |
| Auto-deploy | n/a | GHA on `dev` push | GHA on `v*` tag push (when prod_ready). `main` push only publishes `:latest` — no deploy. |
| Database | bundled container | hosted | hosted (dedicated cluster) |

## Image tags

Passed inline at deploy time, not committed:

```bash
sudo -E USER_SERVICE_TAG=sha-abc1234 CORE_TAG=sha-def5678 \
  docker compose -f staging/docker-compose.yml up -d
```

`-E` is load-bearing — without it sudo strips the exported tags.

## Stop services

```bash
# dev
cd dev && docker compose down
cd dev && docker compose down -v          # also drops bundled DB volume

# staging
sudo docker compose -f staging/docker-compose.yml down

# prod
sudo docker compose -f prod/docker-compose.yml down
```
